.TH "TEMPORAL.ZONEDDATETIME.TOJSON" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.ZonedDateTime.toJSON \-
Temporal.ZonedDateTime.prototype.toJSON()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]toJSON()\f[B]\f[R] method of
\f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] instances returns a string
representing this date\-time in the same RFC 9557 format as calling
\f[CR]toString()\f[R].
It is intended to be implicitly called by \f[CR]JSON.stringify()\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
toJSON()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A string representing the given date\-time in the RFC 9557 format, with
the calendar annotation included if it is not
\f[CR]\(dqiso8601\(dq\f[R], and the offset and time zone annotation
always included.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f[CR]toJSON()\f[R] method is automatically called by
\f[CR]JSON.stringify()\f[R] when a \f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R]
object is stringified.
This method is generally intended to, by default, usefully serialize
\f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] objects during JSON serialization,
which can then be deserialized using the
\f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from()\f[R] function as the reviver of
\f[CR]JSON.parse()\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using toJSON()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] zdt = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from({
  year: 2021,
  month: 8,
  day: 1,
  timeZone: \(dqAmerica/New_York\(dq,
});
\f[B]const\f[R] zdtStr = zdt.toJSON(); \f[I]// \(aq2021\-08\-01T00:00:00\-04:00[America/New_York]\(aq\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] zdt2 = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from(zdtStr);
.EE
.SS JSON serialization and parsing
This example shows how \f[CR]Temporal.ZonedDateTime\f[R] can be
serialized as JSON without extra effort, and how to parse it back.
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] zdt = Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from({
  year: 2021,
  month: 8,
  day: 1,
  timeZone: \(dqAmerica/New_York\(dq,
});
\f[B]const\f[R] jsonStr = JSON.stringify({ meeting: zdt }); \f[I]// \(aq{\(dqmeeting\(dq:\(dq2021\-08\-01T00:00:00\-04:00[America/New_York]\(dq}\(aq\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] obj = JSON.parse(jsonStr, (key, value) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]if\f[R] (key === \(dqmeeting\(dq) {
    \f[B]return\f[R] Temporal.ZonedDateTime.from(value);
  }
  \f[B]return\f[R] value;
});
.EE
